Ah. Gotcha. If it matters, that character in OP is Lynn. She is a wolf. She is an alone wolf, rather than a lone wolf. ("Lone is a choice. Alone is an unfortunate circumstance.") I believe an artist calling himself DeltaV created the character. The running gags--"lore" implies a depth that isn't really there--is that, though she is a member of a highly social carnivore species, she has crippling social anxiety and is a bit of a sperg. She does her best, though, and usually manages to come off looking cute. She is also a bright young woman, when it comes to abstract stuff. She has "buh" as a sort of verbal tic when she gets flustered, and she is flustered most of the time. Her shoulder angel and shoulder devil are flustered all the time too. Lynn is a cute nerd. Lynn is fun to doodle. More than a few people have drawn her. That's all.
